eight=\"964\" data-expand=\"750\" data-srcset=\"https://images.food52.com/gtnxzibzDytTR4n1ScZXUk7hCPg=/375x375/bedcc71f-fece-4c15-9206-f7037942f18d--2020-1001_greentree_handpoured-beeswax-pillar-candles_set-of-6-fall-seasonal_1x1_james-ransom-093.jpg, https://images.food52.com/XFYArNs38yUrdhlXMXZsON-wjpM=/750x750/bedcc71f-fece-4c15-9206-f7037942f18d--2020-1001_greentree_handpoured-beeswax-pillar-candles_set-of-6-fall-seasonal_1x1_james-ransom-093.jpg 2x\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n      \u003cfigcaption\u003e\n\n          \u003cspan\u003ePhoto by James Ransom\u003c/span\u003e\n      \u003c/figcaption\u003e\n  \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n              \u003cp\u003eI light tapers all year round, but something about a winter table with candlelight feels especially cozy. I like how this \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/shop/products/3832-totem-pillar-candles-set-of-3\"\u003eset of pillars\u003c/a\u003e gives you glow and a tablescape all at once, no candle holders needed.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n\n\n  \n\n              \n              \u003cp\u003eIf you’re worried about turnout, I highly recommend you text guests ahead of time that there will be a \u003ca href=\"https://food52.com/recipes/88526-best-cookie-cake-recipe\"\u003ebrown butter cookie cake\u003c/a\u003e so good that the smell of it could wake a sleeping grizzly from hibernation.\u003c/p\u003e\n              \n  \n\n\n\n              \n\n\n              \u003chr/\u003e\n\n              \n              \u003ccenter\u003e\n\u003cem\u003eGot a cozy hosting tip or a go-to winter dish? Drop me a comment—I’d love to hear how you bring everyone together!\u003c/em\u003e\n\u003c/center\u003e\n          \u003c/div\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n            \n            \n\n\n\n            \n\u003cdiv\u003e\n  \n\n    \u003cp\u003e\n      Editorial Director @ Food52\n    \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n  \n  \u003cdiv\u003e\n      \u003ch3\u003ePopular on Food52\u003c/h3\u003e\n      \n    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n  \n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
